Coverage


August 30, 2012
Judge Says Investors Can Demand Ch. 11 Payments From Vitro
A Texas federal judge on Tuesday vacated a bankruptcy court order and said subsidiaries of Vitro SAB de CV haven’t been timely paying down more than $3 billion in debts during a Chapter 11 restructuring and are subject to demands for immediate payment from hedge funds and other investors.





